        {
            "id": "ff3c91bbb54549ae8a16e",
            "questionText": "A transformer in a power distribution system has a primary coil with 500 turns and is connected to an alternating voltage source of 120 V. The magnetic flux in the core changes at a rate of 0.05 Weber/second. If the secondary coil is designed to output 2400 V, determine the rate of change of magnetic flux linkage (in Weber-turns per second) in the secondary coil.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "328c52c4143e46689916d",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the relation that connects the induced electromotive force with the coil turns and the rate of change of magnetic flux. Which formula expresses this relation correctly?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "01f9d96a-7639-4028-8921-a8d295d26596"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\epsilon = N \\frac{d\\Phi}{dt}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\epsilon = \\frac{1}{N} \\frac{d\\Phi}{dt}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\epsilon = B v L$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "ace01fadfee24a7f96fdf",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now let's determine the relationship between the primary and secondary coils of a transformer. Which equation correctly represents the transformer turn ratio?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "01f9d96a-7639-4028-8921-a8d295d26596"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\frac{V_p}{V_s} = \\frac{N_p}{N_s}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\frac{V_p}{V_s} = \\frac{N_s}{N_p}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$V_p \\times V_s = N_p \\times N_s$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "86003589cd0146b491443",
                    "stepText": "Using the transformer relation, calculate the number of turns in the secondary coil. Given that $!$N_p = 500$!$, $!$V_p = 120\\,\\text{V}$!$, and $!$V_s = 2400\\,\\text{V}$!$, compute $!$N_s = (N_p \\times V_s)/V_p$!$. What is the computed value?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "10000"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "turns",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "01f9d96a-7639-4028-8921-a8d295d26596"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "dc39afec6ee2461593fea",
                    "stepText": "Now, calculate the rate of change of magnetic flux linkage in the secondary coil. Multiply the secondary coil turns by the given rate of change of magnetic flux $!$\\frac{d\\Phi}{dt} = 0.05\\,\\text{Weber/s}$!$. What is the final computed value?",
                    "stepText2": "",
